---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";

const REPO = "https://github.com/0x-copilot-dev/0x-copilot";
const DISCORD = "https://discord.com/invite/NhCv7zDkmX";
const X = "https://x.com/Copilot0x";
---

<Base
  title="Tokenomics — 0xCopilot"
  description="50% fair launch, 25% team & contributors, 25% automated capital formation. Every allocation has a job. No pre-buy, no hidden fourth bucket."
>
  <Nav />

  <header class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="pill"><span class="dot"></span> Not launched · no contract address exists yet</span>
      <h1>Every allocation has <em>a job.</em></h1>
      <p class="sub">
        0xCopilot launches on Virtuals Protocol. Three buckets, no hidden fourth.
        Half the supply belongs to the market from the first block, a quarter is
        reserved for the people who build the thing, and a quarter is a funding
        engine the protocol runs — <b>not a wallet anyone can reach into.</b>
      </p>
      <div class="bar" role="img" aria-label="50% fair launch, 25% ESOP, 25% automated capital formation">
        <div class="seg mkt">50%&nbsp; Fair launch</div>
        <div class="seg bld">25%&nbsp; ESOP</div>
        <div class="seg pro">25%&nbsp; ACF</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="sec" style="border-top:none;padding-top:8px">
    <div class="wrap">
      <!-- 50% market -->
      <div class="tk-bucket">
        <div class="tk-pct mkt">50%<span>The market</span></div>
        <div class="tk-body">
          <h3>Fair launch — tradable from the first block.</h3>
          <p>Half the supply, in the pool, at launch. No lock, no vesting, no allowlist, no preferential price. Everyone holding this half bought it on the open curve at the same public price as everyone else.</p>
          <p><b>There is no founder pre-buy.</b> No insider bucket sits in front of the market on the curve. The largest single allocation in this project belongs to the people who buy it.</p>
          <ul class="tk-facts">
            <li><b>Lock</b><span>None — live at launch.</span></li>
            <li><b>Float</b><span>Grows one buy at a time. The pool is inventory, not a holder.</span></li>
            <li><b>Supply</b><span><span class="tbd">FILL: fixed supply</span> — set at launch under the Virtuals framework and published here before the first block.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 25% people -->
      <div class="tk-bucket">
        <div class="tk-pct">25%<span>The people</span></div>
        <div class="tk-body">
          <h3>Team &amp; contributors — the ESOP pool.</h3>
          <p>Reserved for the people who ship the product. Not a founder allocation — a pool that pays out as grants to the engineers, designers and contributors who actually build 0xCopilot, each grant carrying its own vesting on top of the protocol lock.</p>
          <p>Unallocated tokens sit still in a published wallet. A transfer out of this pool means a person joined — nothing else.</p>
          <ul class="tk-facts">
            <li><b>Protocol lock</b><span><span class="tbd">FILL: lock period</span> from launch, enforced on-chain by Virtuals.</span></li>
            <li><b>Protocol vest</b><span><span class="tbd">FILL: vest window + shape</span> into a pool wallet the company controls.</span></li>
            <li><b>Grants</b><span>Made from the pool with their own multi-year schedule and cliff, sized by role. A grant re-locks; it does not unlock.</span></li>
            <li><b>Early vest</b><span><span class="tbd">FILL: FDV early-vest trigger, if any</span> — Virtuals can start the vest early above a valuation threshold. If that applies here it gets stated on this line, not discovered later.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- 25% engine -->
      <div class="tk-bucket">
        <div class="tk-pct">25%<span>The engine</span></div>
        <div class="tk-body">
          <h3>Automated Capital Formation — funding tied to proof.</h3>
          <p>The funding engine, executed by the protocol rather than by anyone's judgment. As valuation rises, ACF converts tokens to USDC in small automated steps and routes the proceeds to the operating company — hiring, infrastructure, audits, the work.</p>
          <p><b>No growth, no funding.</b> Capital only forms when the market has verified the work. There is no discretionary insider selling from this bucket, because no insider can execute it.</p>
          <ul class="tk-facts">
            <li><b>Trigger</b><span><span class="tbd">FILL: starting FDV</span> — below that, ACF releases nothing.</span></li>
            <li><b>Mechanism</b><span>Automated conversion at each additional <span class="tbd">FILL: FDV step</span>, continuing to <span class="tbd">FILL: FDV ceiling</span>.</span></li>
            <li><b>Proceeds</b><span>USDC growth capital to the operating company.</span></li>
            <li><b>Execution</b><span>Protocol-run and on-chain. Not a wallet with a human signer.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kick">Day one</p>
      <h2>Insider-linked supply that can move at launch: zero.</h2>
      <p class="lede">Only fair-launch tokens can trade on day one. The ESOP is behind a protocol lock, ACF hasn't triggered, and there is no pre-buy to unlock. Every insider-linked token is locked, vested, or protocol-executed.</p>
      <p class="note">
        <b>Where the operating money comes from.</b> Day-to-day costs are meant to
        run on the protocol's trade-fee stream, not on selling supply — and scale
        capital comes from ACF, which only fires when valuation rises.
        <span class="tbd">FILL: fee split + operations share</span> once the launch
        parameters are fixed, so this line matches what's actually on-chain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="kick">Commitments</p>
      <h2>The rules we hold ourselves to.</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="qa"><div class="q">Every wallet is published</div><div class="a">The ESOP pool and the company treasury are labeled and watchable on-chain from day one. There are no allocations other than the three on this page.</div></div>
        <div class="qa"><div class="q">The ESOP moves only by grant</div><div class="a">Unallocated tokens sit visibly still. A transfer out means a person joined.</div></div>
        <div class="qa"><div class="q">No founder pre-buy</div><div class="a">At launch or after, from any bucket on this page.</div></div>
        <div class="qa"><div class="q">The protocol holds the keys</div><div class="a">Locks, vesting and ACF execution are enforced on-chain by Virtuals — the parts you'd otherwise have to trust are the parts we can't touch.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="legal">
        <p>The 0xCopilot token is not equity, and carries no dividend, revenue entitlement, or claim on company assets. Nothing on this page is an offer of securities or investment advice.</p>
        <p>Protocol mechanics — locks, vesting and ACF thresholds — follow the Virtuals Protocol framework and are enforced on-chain. The ESOP grant policy is a 0xCopilot commitment, published here and verifiable by watching the labeled wallets.</p>
        <p><b style="color:var(--sky)">No contract address exists yet.</b> When one does it will be published here and on <a href={X} rel="noopener">@Copilot0x</a>. Any address you see anywhere else, before then, is not ours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="frow">
        <span class="wm" style="font-size:22px">0x<b>Copilot</b></span>
        <div class="flinks">
          <a href="./">Home</a>
          <a href={REPO} rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
          <a href={DISCORD} rel="noopener">Discord ↗</a>
          <a href={X} rel="noopener">@Copilot0x ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="foot-b">
        <span>© 2026 0xCopilot · Ask · Steer · Ship</span>
        <span class="ass">Nothing on this site is financial advice or an offer of securities.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
